summary: I know that the first Spider-man movie was a long time ago, i remember going to the theatre and seeing it. And there have been a...
body:
I know that the first Spider-man movie was a long time ago, i remember going to the theatre and seeing it. And there have been a lot of spider-man movies since then, but this part will remain one of my favorite scene

I know the cgi is outdated, but I always loved that the people on the bridge and the boat tried to help him. It’s one thing to see a million super hero movies about superheroes, but seeing regular citizens stand up for others?

That’s cool

summary: I know that the Andrew Garfield Spider-Man movies are unpopular with a lot of people but I gotta say...one of my personal...
body:
I know that the Andrew Garfield Spider-Man movies are unpopular with a lot of people but I gotta say…one of my personal favorite movie scenes is when he comes home battered and bloodied from the events of the night. Aunt May watches him slowly limp over to her and he reaches into his backpack. He pulls out a carton of eggs that she asked him to get from the store earlier in the movie and she pulls him in and hugs him. I think about it a lot

(Source)
